cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with saliency models and their performance evaluation using synthetic image datasets. Additionally, the paper also discusses the consistency of these models with human psychophysics, which falls under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of deep learning models in the study also suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of low-level features in the synthetic images and the evaluation of model performance using saliency metrics suggest that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
